ating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Composable Architecture to 1.15.0 should not cause any compilation errors. However, if you have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strict concurrency turned on, then you may come across a few situations you need to update.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Enum cases as function references","type":"heading","anchor":"Enum-cases-as-function-references","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is common to use the case of enum as a function, such as mapping on an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect"},{"type":"text","text":" to bundle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its output into an action:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["return client.fetch()","  .map(Action.response)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In strict concurrency mode this may fail with a message like this:","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"🛑 Converting non-sendable function value to ‘@Sendable (Value) -> Action’ may introduce data races"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two ways to fix this. You can either open the closure explicitly instead of using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Action.response","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as a function:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["return client.fetch()","  .map { .response($0) }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is also an upcoming Swift feature that will fix this. You can enable it in an SPM package","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by adding a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enableUpcomingFeature"},{"text":" to its Swift settings:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["swiftSettings: [","  .enableUpcomingFeature(\"InferSendableFromCaptures\"),","]),"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And you can "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/blog\/using-upcoming-feature-flags\/"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by navigating to your project’s build settings in Xcode, and adding a new “Other Swift Flags” flag:"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["-enable-upcoming-feature InferSendableFromCaptures"]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The library has been completely updated for Swift 6 language mode, and now compiles in strict","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"concurrency with no warnings or errors.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Migrating to 1.15","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}]},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.15"]}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.16":{"url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.16","title":"Migrating to 1.16","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":".appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" strategy used with ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" now uses key-value observing instead of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NotificationCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when possible. Learn how this may affect your code.","type":"te